<br>
- Druid/Shm call to corpse<br>
- Wiz secondary bind, punt group to bind<br>
- Monk Fade<br>
- Chanter stasis<br>
- Cleric sanctuary<br>
etc.<br>
<br>
I will ignore the melee based ones, since it is just silly to even discuss riposte or shielding effects of our offhand strikes~<br>
<br>
Bards get Infuriate (AE ramp with our paltry DPS), which makes no sense due to massive mob DPS.  Any time I have more than one mob in camp, it will be mezzed, not tickled by my EoE.  Only useful in AE encounters, where it wont matter anyways.  <br>
<br>
Bards get 1 min increase to hate from detrimental songs; is this a joke?  For the rare times I might want agro, if it isn't snap agro, it wont help.  Not to mention, if I am in a group, I ave 4 beneficial songs and 4 utility songs memmed.  If tank dies and I want agro, I will have to sit to mem the right spell set anyways.  Cleric wil be dead by this point.  <br>
<br>
Bards get to spend a ton of AA for AA bellow upgrade to add up to 50 dmg every 18 secs, and interrupt spell casting.  And I would do this instead of mez why?  <br>
<br>
Very unhappy with the AA's so far.  I think we should be complaining about this now, since it will be near impossible once it goes live.<br>
<br>
I think we should definitely get a personal DPS upgrade, something along the lines of 100pct chance to DW and DA, letting us quad for 1 min, with a decent refresh (10/20 min).  Also agree on the above instrument suggestions.  Make it worthwhile to use an instrument again.<br>
<br>
While Dire charm would be fun, it would be a PITA if you hit fade and then have to deal with ex-pet.  The swarm pet idea is good as well.<br>
<br>
Kanarian, Bard of Saryrn<br>
